# Multi-Role Architecture & UX Overhaul (Approved)

## Key Decisions from User Feedback
- **Unique IDs** for every account type: `clinic_id`, `doctor_id`, `receptionist_id` — for production support
- **Doctor analytics** — YES, but scoped to their own patients only
- **Receptionist patients tab** — show patient records with timing history (in/out)
- **Doctor visibility** — own patients only by default; clinic account has toggles per doctor (show all patients, schedules, etc.)
- **Existing doctor accounts** — delete all, not needed
- **Payment prep** — add `subscription_tier`, `is_trial`, `max_doctors` on clinics; `is_paid` on doctors
- **PB receptionists collection** — user creates manually, instructions provided below

---

## PocketBase: Create `receptionists` Auth Collection

1. Open PocketBase Admin → **Collections** → **New collection**
2. Name: `receptionists`, Type: **Auth**
3. Add these fields:
   - `name` — Text (required)
   - `phone` — Text (optional)
   - `clinic` — Relation → `clinics` (required, single)
   - `is_active` — Bool (default: true)  
   - `receptionist_id` — Text (unique) — auto-generated unique ID for support
4. **API Rules** tab:
   - List/Search rule: `clinic = @request.auth.clinic || @request.auth.id = clinic`
   - View rule: same as above
   - Create rule: (leave empty — only admins/clinic-side code creates)
   - Update rule: `id = @request.auth.id`
   - Delete rule: (leave empty — admin only)
5. Also add to `doctors` collection: a field `doctor_id` (Text, unique) if not present
6. Also add to `clinics` collection (if not present): `subscription_tier` (Text, default "free"), `max_doctors` (Number, default 1)

---

## Execution Phases

### Phase 1: Auth Core (UserRole, models, services)
### Phase 2: Login & Registration UI
### Phase 3: MainLayout with PageView swipe + role-based tabs
### Phase 4: Receptionist dashboard + restricted UI
### Phase 5: Doctor management + visibility toggles (Settings)
### Phase 6: Notification preferences
### Phase 7: Appointments UX (Today button, scroll, highlight)
